The IEBC has been urged not to clear governor aspirants who have refused to honour the Senate Public Accounts Committee summonses.Kiambu Senator Kimani Wamatangi (pictured) yesterday said governors should be accountable and should respect Senate summons.The senator said such governors are not fit to hold a public office.&ldquo;It is not negotiable on the issues of the Constitution. Public officers swear to comply and abide by the Constitution,&rdquo; Wamatangi said.He said the Senate is a creation of the Constitution and it should be respected once summons are made and recommendations made by the House members followed.Wamatangi said some governors cannot be allowed to escape appearing before the committee to defend their expenditures of public funds.